section.section:
To carry out the requirements of this section, the Board:
May establish and abolish positions;
May determine employee qualifications;
May establish terms of employment, including compensation, benefits, holiday schedules, and leave policies;
May determine any other matters concerning employees; and
Shall designate one or more representatives to participate as a party in collective bargaining on behalf of the College in accordance with Title 3 of the State Personnel and Pensions Article.
